<br>
<br>
Yes it does have to be this way, and Emil's post does answer your question.  Doing it any other way is counter to the whole concept of rotating mobs to share amongst those who can benefit from the mobs in question.  The Named without Dozekar are nothing.  Dozekar without the Named is nothing.  To use rotations to your favor (i.e. ensure you get shots at Dozekar) and then ignoring the parts you don't like (i.e. wanting to grab not just your share of Drakes, but everyone's) is greedy and self-centered.<br>
<br>
As for your VP analogy, if the symbols for Doze quests were 8 hour ground spawns all over Velious, I can promise you, NB would have a lot more Doze quests completed.  I would also say that anyone not in a guild that kills Trakanon who collects VP key pieces is wasting their bank space.  I would say the same about VT shards.  If you aren't in a guild actively gathering Emperor keys, you are just wasting your bank space and preventing other players who can use those items better.<br>
<br>
Thirdly, I would caution you about trying to make the Named Drakes FFA, as I would make sure that NB took full advantage of said system, if only to prove a point that rotations benefit you a lot more than they do &quot;the big guilds&quot;.  I prefer to share the pie as equally as possible, but if you don't want to play nice on the playground, we can go that way too. <p><p><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net"><img src="http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif" align="left" border="0"></a>Karadin Firethorne<br>Assassin of The Rathe<br><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net">Noble Blade</a> 
